- When migrating from the old architecture to the new one, ALWAYS remember (and refactor the file to meet these requirements):
    - If necessary, split services into repositories, freezed models and providers
    - If necessary, split widgets into state models, providers and stateless widgets
    - Don't use relative paths in imports
    - Aim to break down complex widget trees into smaller, reusable components
    - If there's any methods that return widgets, transform them into smaller widgets instead of methods
    - AppColors are located in `@lib/src/core/theme/data/models/colors.dart`
    - Get all theming information from the context
    - All ATProto endpoints are in `@lib/lexicons/`, create models if needed
    - For storage, get a storage manager from the get it
    - For cache, get a cache manager interface from the get it
    - For logging, use the logging framework
    - For auth, get a AuthRepository from the get it
    - For API calls, check if `@lib/src/core/network/data/repositories/sprk_repository.dart` already has that method in its contract
        - If it does, get it from the get it
    - Don't forget to add repositories to the service locator at `@lib/src/core/di/service_locator.dart`
    - For navigation, use the AutoRoute package and register routes at `@lib/src/core/routing/app_router.dart`
    - DO NOT import ANYTHING from the old architecture